Conditional statements
--used to decide whether the code has to be executed or skipped based only when the given condition is true
--to make the set of instructions execute only when the condition is true. 
--it executes in a sequence I.e, line by line
Block of code: set of instructions:
--It will execute only when the specific condition is true.
Condition: An expression that evaluates a result in the form of true or false.
Example: 
        let a=4
        let b=5
        if(a<b){
            document.write("hello jayadeep",",<br>")
        }
        document.write("brilliant me!!")
Output: 
hello jayadeep
brilliant me!!
Ex: console.log(5>6)
--Methods:
1.If statement
2.If-else
3.Else-if
4.Switch
5.Ternary operator

If: Only one possible condition . If the condition is true then it will execute, otherwise it will be skipped.
Syntax:
If(condition){
--block of code //executed only when the condition is satisfied
}
